Anthocleista nobilis

    Authority   G. Don
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Asteridae:Gentianales:Gentianaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 3260

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A medium-sized tree reaching up to 20 m in height and
   a trunk diameter of 50-90 cm. The bark is light grey and smooth, with
   the bole free of branches up to 15 m. The leaves is oblong-elliptic,
   obovate-elliptic or oblong-lanceolate, 6.5-40 cm long and 4-12 cm wide.
   The fruits are dark brown ellipsoid berries, 2-2.5 cm in diameter. USES
   The bark has medicinal properties. GROWING PERIOD Perennial. COMMON
   NAMES Carbage tree, Cabbage palm, Hororoho, Awudifoakete, Bontodi.
   FURTHER INF Scientific synonym: A. parviflora. Carbage tree can be
   found in transitional and secondary forests. It generally prefers low
   lying ground not exceeding 300 m above sea level but can occur up to
   1200 m. It occurs on the west coast of Africa from Senegal to Nigeria.
   Cases of accidental poisonings have been reported.

   Sources
   Iwu M 1993 pp 118-120 [DRA, RAIN, TEMP, LIMITS]

